The **items grid** is wired up in three places:

### 1. Layout & columns — `app/index.tsx`

The two-column masonry (`LEFT_PRODUCTS` / `RIGHT_PRODUCTS`), widths, gutter, and left-column offset live in the Discover screen around the “MASONRY PRODUCT GRID” block:

```268:293:c:\Users\debob\Desktop\GymBros TakeHome\app\index.tsx
        {/* ── MASONRY PRODUCT GRID (same width as hero / Figma Items 1:67) ───── */}
        <View style={[styles.grid, { gap: colGap }]}>
          {/* Left column — starts 31pt lower per Figma (node 1:69 top=31) */}
          <View style={[styles.column, { width: colW, marginTop: 31 * scale }]}>
            {LEFT_PRODUCTS.map((product, i) => (
              <ProductCard
                key={product.id}
                product={product}
                index={i * 2}
                column="left"
                onPress={handleProductPress}
              />
            ))}
          </View>

          <View style={[styles.column, { width: colW }]}>
            {RIGHT_PRODUCTS.map((product, i) => (
              <ProductCard
                key={product.id}
                product={product}
                index={i * 2 + 1}
                column="right"
                onPress={handleProductPress}
              />
            ))}
          </View>
        </View>
```

Supporting math for **`cardW`**, **`colGap`**, **`colW`**, **`scale`** is a bit higher in the same file (around the `useWindowDimensions` / `scale` block).

### 2. Each cell — `components/ProductCard.tsx`

Renders a single grid item (image, heart, text, animations, etc.).

### 3. Data & column split — `constants/products.ts`

**`PRODUCTS`**, **`LEFT_PRODUCTS`**, and **`RIGHT_PRODUCTS`** define which products go in which column and their `cardHeight` hints for masonry.

